{
  "texts": [
    "k i=1 stands for the sum of images' possible values, given a discrete class membership Y and probability p of class i.",
    "Only images with entropy (> 0.6) were assigned for manual annotation and then later added to the training pool.",
    "The process was repeated two times until the best accuracy was obtained for all the classes.",
    "In total, 716 labeled images from the training pool were used in the initial training.",
    "In the second cycle using AL, we annotated 372 images which were then added to the training pool for second round of model training, followed by 554 images for the third AL training cycle, Figure 9."
  ]
